@[Thiago] @[Anderson] Let's discuss about the solution. I just saw that you configured both png and jpg to use webp format. But this does not match what we discussed some weeks ago. In my view, ideally we will configure formats for avif, webp and jpg like so:

```    presets: {
      webp: {
        modifiers: {
          format: 'webp',
          loading: 'lazy',
          quality: '80',
        },
      },```
Then we can put this:

`format: ["avif", "webp", "jpeg"]`

As a result, all images should then use avif -&gt; webp -&gt; jpeg, depending on browser support. Then we don't need to specify file format explicity on any images, as by default it will always choose the correct one.

What do you think?

Maybe it would be:

```    presets: {
      photo: {
        modifiers: {
          format: ["avif", "webp", "jpeg"]
          loading: 'lazy',
          quality: '80',
        },
      },
      diagram: {
        modifiers: {
          format: ["avif", "webp", "png"]
          loading: 'lazy',
          quality: '80',
        },
      },```
By the way, what about different sizes for mobile and desktop? Do we have to do something here?

For now we should do it like this:

```export default defineNuxtConfig({
  modules: [
    '@nuxt/image'
  ],
  image: {
    // Default image provider and other options
    providers: {
      // ... you might have other providers here
    },
    // Include jpeg in generated formats
    formats: {
      jpeg: {} // You can add quality settings here
    }
  }
})```
```&lt;template&gt;
  &lt;nuxt-img src="/my-image.png" width="600" height="400" format="jpeg" /&gt; 
&lt;/template&gt;```

